revision.text:
{{High-use}}
{{Documentation subpage}}
<!-- Place categories where indicated at the bottom of this page and interwikis at Wikidata (see [[Wikipedia:Wikidata]]) -->
Extract a 4-digit decade from the page title, without the trailing "s".

e.g. from "Lorem ipsum dolor 1510s it amet"  it will extract "1510"

Note that the trailing letter "s" is stripped, to allow manipulation.  In template coding, it can be easily be added after the template call, e.g. {{nowrap|<code><nowiki>Famine in the {{Title decade}}</nowiki>'''s'''<nowiki> in Atlantis</nowiki></code>.}}

== Usage ==
{{tlx|Title decade|''match''|''nomatch''|4=page=}}

or 

{{tlx|Title decade|<nowiki>match=|nomatch=|page=</nowiki>}}

=== Decade from title which contains only a year ===
Note also that this template will ''not'' return the decade from a title which includes only a year.
e.g.
* <code><nowiki>{{Title decade|page=Horticultural controversies in the 1790s in Xanadu}}</nowiki></code> → {{Title decade|page=Horticultural controversies in the 1790s in Xanadu}}
* <code><nowiki>{{Title decade|page=Horticultural controversies in 1797 in Xanadu}}</nowiki></code> → {{Title decade|page=Horticultural controversies in 1797 in Xanadu}}

However, the decade can easily be obtained by using {{tl|DECADE}} as a wrapper around {{tl|Title year}}: <code><nowiki>{{DECADE|{{Title year}}}}</nowiki></code>.

<code><nowiki>{{Title year|page=1953 riots in Narnia}}</nowiki></code> → {{Title year|page=1953 riots in Narnia}}
<br>and<br><code><nowiki>{{DECADE|1953}}</nowiki></code> → {{DECADE|1953}}
<br>... so<br><code><nowiki>{{DECADE|{{Title year|page=1953 riots in Narnia}}}}</nowiki></code> → {{DECADE|{{Title year|page=1953 riots in Narnia}}}}

== TemplateData ==
{{TemplateData header}}
<templatedata>
{
	"params": {
		"1": {
			"aliases": [
				"match"
			],
			"label": "Match Instance",
			"description": "If multiple 4-digit decades are found, this specifies which match to return, where the first match is match= 1. If a negative number is specified then a match is returned counting from the last match. Hence match = -1 is the same as requesting the last match. Defaults to 1.",
			"type": "number",
			"default": "1"
		},
		"2": {
			"aliases": [
				"nomatch"
			],
			"label": "No match text",
			"description": "If no 4-digit decades is found, output the \"nomatch\" value. Defaults to blank.",
			"type": "string"
		},
		"page": {
			"label": "Override page title",
			"description": "Specified a page title to use other than the current page. If left blank, the template will use the title of the current page",
			"type": "wiki-page-name",
			"default": "{{BASEPAGENAME}}"
		}
	},
	"description": "Extracts a 4-digit decade from the current page title. All parameters are optional."
}
</templatedata>

== See also ==
{{Columns-list|
* [[Template:Decade link]]
{{Title year see also}}
}}

{{string-handling templates}}

